  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (United States)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Regulatory Measures:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Enhanced financial transparency\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n4. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement anti-money laundering programs\n- Regular reporting and record-keeping\n- Training employees on detecting suspicious transactions\n- Implementing robust screening processes\n\n5. Penalties:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecutions\n- Asset seizures\n- Potential business license revocation\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
